SIMPLE: environment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Environment
<hw>En*vi"ron*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>environnement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of environing;
state of being environed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which environs or surrounds; surrounding
conditions, influences, or forces, by which living forms are influenced
and modified in their growth and development.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is no friendly <qex>environment</qex>, this of thine.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>environmental</ent>⟦br⟧
